<item>
            <title>[MJAVADOC-220] ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException in JavadocUtil.getIncludedFiles</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MJAVADOC-220</link>
                <project id="12317529" key="MJAVADOC">Maven Javadoc Plugin (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When executing javadoc:jar with &amp;lt;excludePackageNames&amp;gt;*&amp;lt;/excludePackageNames&amp;gt; (or other values)  we get :&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;java.lang.ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException: 0&lt;br/&gt;
        at org.apache.maven.plugin.javadoc.JavadocUtil.getIncludedFiles(JavadocUtil.java:369)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is probably related to this code :&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;String[] excludeName = excludePackages&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;k&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;.split( &quot;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;*&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&quot; );&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;br/&gt;
 if ( excludeName.length &amp;gt; 1 )&lt;br/&gt;
{&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;br/&gt;
} &lt;br/&gt;
else &lt;br/&gt;
{&lt;br/&gt;
     if ( fileList&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;j&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;.startsWith( sourceDirectory.toString() + File.separatorChar + excludeName&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; ) )&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If the split() function returns an empty array (excludeName), we reach the &quot;else&quot; branch but &quot;excludeName&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&quot; will throw java.lang.ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException: 0&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>maven 2.0.9 windows xp</environment>
